<HEADLINE>
2 INJURED IN HONG KONG TOUR GROUP BUS MISHAP IN CHIAYI
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, April 30 (CNA) 04/30/07  23:37:59 (By Sofia Wu)
</P>
<P>
A tour bus carrying 15 passengers -- 13 of them tourists from
Hong Kong -- accidentally hit an electric pole in a scenic
mountainous area in the southern county of Chiayi, leaving three
men and one woman injured, local police said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Among the injured, a Taiwanese tour guide was more seriously
injured than any of the other three Hong Kong tourists, the
police said.
</P>
<P>
All are conscious and none are in critical condition, the police
explained.
</P>
<P>
After treatment, two Hong Kong tourists were discharged from the
hospital and joined the tour group to continue their journey.
</P>
<P>
Only the Taiwan tour guide and one Hong Kong tourist still remain
in the hospital for observation.
</P>
<P>
The bus was touring Alishan, a mountain resort in the southern
county,  when the accident occurred, police said, adding that
visibility at the time was very poor due to heavy fog.
</P>
<P>
The police are still investigating the cause of the accident.
</P>
